item.title: Autonomous vechicle microsleep detector Vol2: Modelling
item.description: Autonomous vehicles are no longer reserved for the realm of science fiction, but some AI experts say the complexities of AI-driven cars in public make the possibility of never needing to drive a far off future. Perhaps to bridge the gap are technologies that greatly reduce the labour involved in driving, while still reducing the risk.
